### ClickNBack — Workflow 3: Purchase Ingestion and Cashback Calculation
###
### Goal: Simulate a purchase event from an external merchant system,
###       confirm it, and verify that cashback is calculated and credited.
### Roles: Admin (ingestion + confirmation), User (viewing results)
###
### Prerequisites:
###   - An active merchant with an active offer exists (run 01-admin-platform-setup.http).
###   - A registered user exists (run 02-user-discovery.http).
###
### ⚪ STATUS: These endpoints are BACKLOG — fully specified but not yet implemented.
###    This file documents the intended API surface so you can understand the
###    domain model and prepare integration tests ahead of time.
###
### Live API: https://clicknback.com
### Docs:     https://clicknback.com/docs

@baseUrl = https://clicknback.com


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 1 — Login as admin
#
# The purchase ingestion endpoint is authenticated (system/admin role).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name adminLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "carol@clicknback.com",
  "password": "Str0ng!Pass"
}


###

@adminToken = PASTE_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE
@merchantId = PASTE_MERCHANT_ID_FROM_WORKFLOW_1_HERE
@userId     = PASTE_USER_ID_FROM_WORKFLOW_2_HERE


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# STEP 2 — Ingest a purchase (webhook call from external merchant system)

# Confirmation is now handled asynchronously by a background job. There is no public API endpoint for manual confirmation.
#
# Expected: 201 Created with status: "pending" and cashback_amount: 0.
# Copy the `id` value and set @purchaseId below.
#
# Business rules:
#   - This endpoint is IDEMPOTENT: submitting the same external_id twice
#     returns the existing purchase — no duplicate is created.
#   - The purchase starts in "pending" state; cashback is not calculated yet.
#   - external_id is the merchant's own transaction ID (any unique string).
#   - amount is in the currency specified (EUR in this demo).
#
# Try idempotency: send this request twice — the second call returns the
# existing purchase with 200 OK instead of 201 Created.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name ingestPurchase
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "external_id": "txn_demo_001",
  "user_id": "{{userId}}",
  "merchant_id": "{{merchantId}}",
  "amount": 100.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}


###

@purchaseId = PASTE_PURCHASE_ID_HERE


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 2b — Test idempotency: send the SAME purchase again
#
# Expected: the existing purchase is returned unchanged. No duplicate is created.
# The cashback is not double-counted.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "external_id": "txn_demo_001",
  "user_id": "{{userId}}",
  "merchant_id": "{{merchantId}}",
  "amount": 100.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 3 — Confirm the purchase
#
# Transitions the purchase from "pending" → "confirmed".
# Expected: 200 OK. At this point:
#   1. The system finds the active offer for this merchant on the purchase date.
#   2. Calculates cashback (e.g., 5% of €100 = €5.00), subject to monthly_cap.
#   3. Credits the user's wallet with a "pending" cashback transaction.
#
# If no active offer existed for this merchant on the purchase date, cashback = 0.
#
# Business rule: once confirmed, a purchase cannot be re-confirmed. Use the
# reverse endpoint (step 6) to undo.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/confirm
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 4 — Login as the user to view their purchase history
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name userLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "Alice1234!"
}


###

@userToken = PASTE_USER_TOKEN_HERE


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 5 — List the user's purchases
#
# Expected: paginated list of purchases with status, amount, and cashback_amount.
# Confirmed purchases show the calculated cashback.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{userId}}/purchases?page=1&page_size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 5b — View a specific purchase's details
#
# Expected: full purchase object including cashback_amount, status, and
# the offer details that were applied.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases/{{purchaseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 6 (optional) — Reverse a purchase
#
# Use this to simulate a refund or fraud reversal.
# Expected: purchase transitions to "reversed" state.
# Cashback that was credited is clawed back from the user's wallet.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases/{{purchaseId}}/reverse
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ADMIN VIEW — List all purchases (admin only, paginated)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases?page=1&page_size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
